The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Sheikh Salim, 28, was arrested on Friday morning for duping a girl of ornaments worth thousands of rupees on May 29. Police said Salim had told ?girlfriend? Kajoli Sarkar, 21, a resident of Jadavpur, that he would take her to his parents. Following his advice, Kajoli came wearing gold ornaments.

 he two went to a mall on VIP Road, where Salim asked Kajoli to keep her ornaments in a bag to ward off snatchers. Salim held the bag himself.

 fter a while, he fled with the bag. Kajoli later lodged a police complaint. 

 Arun Mahapatra, 34, a sergeant at Taratala police station, was hit by a car around 1.40 pm on Taratala Road. Police said the sergeant was on his regular rounds. He was admitted to BP Poddar Hospital. The driver fled. 

 A 28-year-old autorickshaw driver, Saikat Halder, was allegedly beaten up by policemen in Bansdroni on Thursday after he refused to pay Rs 10 to a traffic cop. Halder was admitted to hospital. A police complaint has been lodged.

 Bishu Dutta, 35, died after being knocked down by a private bus in Golabari, Howrah, on Friday. Dutta, a resident of Thakurpukur, was taken to hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

